        <mxCell id="p1t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#856404;" value="Why Blanket Human Review Fails" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="18" width="356" x="22" y="88" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=10;fontColor=#5A6A80;" value="98% approval rates in 2 seconds is liability theater, not oversight" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="14" width="356" x="22" y="106" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1div" parent="1" style="line;strokeColor=#FFCA2C;fillColor=none;strokeWidth=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="4" width="368" x="16" y="124" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1b" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#7A6000;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Volume: 500+ decisions/day produces rubber-stamping, not review.&#xa;&#xa;Velocity: Real-time pipelines cannot pause for human deliberation.&#xa;&#xa;Context collapse: An approve/reject button is not a review interface.&#xa;&#xa;Result: When humans approve 98% of agent decisions in under 2 seconds, errors pass through at full speed and the organization develops false confidence in a safety layer that is not functioning." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="134" width="362" x="22" y="132" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2bg" parent="1" style="rounded=1;arcSize=3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#CBD8EF;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="196" width="392" x="404" y="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2bar" parent="1" style="rounded=0;fillColor=#1B3A6B;strokeColor=none;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="5" width="392" x="404" y="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1B3A6B;" value="The Autonomy Spectrum: 3 Levels" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="18" width="364" x="418" y="88" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=10;fontColor=#5A6A80;" value="Determined by criteria, not convenience" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="14" width="364" x="418" y="106" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2div" parent="1" style="line;strokeColor=#E0E8F4;fillColor=none;strokeWidth=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="4" width="376" x="412" y="124" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2b" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="IN the loop: Human approves each decision. High consequence, low volume, pause-tolerant. &#xa;&#xa;ON the loop: Agents run autonomously, humans monitor and intervene on anomalies. High volume with bounded blast radius. &#xa;&#xa;OUT of the loop: Full automation. Humans own design and aggregate oversight. Requires the most engineering rigor — not the least." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="134" width="370" x="418" y="132" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3bg" parent="1" style="rounded=1;arcSize=3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#CBD8EF;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="196" width="384" x="808" y="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3bar" parent="1" style="rounded=0;fillColor=#1B3A6B;strokeColor=none;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="5" width="384" x="808" y="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1B3A6B;" value="Five-Criteria Checkpoint Design" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="18" width="356" x="822" y="88" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=10;fontColor=#5A6A80;" value="A checkpoint earns its place only if it clears 3 of 5" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="14" width="356" x="822" y="106" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3div" parent="1" style="line;strokeColor=#E0E8F4;fillColor=none;strokeWidth=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="4" width="368" x="816" y="124" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p3b" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="1. Consequence: blast radius of agent error at this point &#xa;2. Frequency: deliberation feasible at this volume? &#xa;3. Human value: does human genuinely improve decision? &#xa;4. Latency tolerance: can the workflow pause? &#xa;5. Auditability: compliance requires human record? &#xa;&#xa;Auditability = HIGH always triggers checkpoint regardless of other scores." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="134" width="362" x="822" y="132" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4bg" parent="1" style="rounded=1;arcSize=3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#CBD8EF;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="196" width="384" x="8" y="286" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4bar" parent="1" style="rounded=0;fillColor=#1B3A6B;strokeColor=none;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="5" width="384" x="8" y="286" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1B3A6B;" value="Escalation Path: 5 Required Components" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="18" width="356" x="22" y="294" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=10;fontColor=#5A6A80;" value="Design all five before the checkpoint goes live" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="14" width="356" x="22" y="312" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4div" parent="1" style="line;strokeColor=#E0E8F4;fillColor=none;strokeWidth=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="4" width="368" x="16" y="330" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4b" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="1. Routing: who is notified, which channel, what SLA &#xa;2. Context package: reasoning trace, confidence distribution, consequence map &#xa;3. Authority clarity: exactly what choices the human can make &#xa;4. Response handling: structured schema for agent to consume decision &#xa;5. Timeout and fallback: what happens when no response arrives  &#39;Wait indefinitely&#39; is not a valid production fallback." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="134" width="362" x="22" y="338" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5bg" parent="1" style="rounded=1;arcSize=3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFDF0;strokeColor=#FFCA2C;" value="" vertex="1">
